===Smartphone app===
The studio [[DLE (company)|DLE]] also produced a smartphone app, titled {{nihongo|''Q Transformers: Return of the Mystery of Convoy''|キュートランスフォーマー 帰ってきたコンボイの謎|Kyū Toransufōmā Kaettekita Konboi no Nazo}}, which was released for [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] devices in August 2014.<ref name="animenewsnetwork.com"/> This was a remake of the original game using Q Transformers [[Optimus Prime]] and [[Bumblebee (Transformers)|Bumblebee]] as playable characters instead of [[Ultra Magnus]] and [[Rodimus Prime]]. Like the original, it is quite difficult but serves as an endless runner game instead of the platformer style of the original. This was a Japanese app store exclusive, but the servers have been shut down since its release.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.appspy.com/news/8947/transformers-nes-game-returns-as-q-transformers-mystery-of-the-returned-convoy-on-ios-and-android | title=Transformers NES game returns as Q Transformers: Mystery of the Returned Convoy on iOS and Android}}</ref>

==Reception==
''Transformers: Mystery of Convoy'' is known for its high difficulty level and poor stage design, resulting in a largely negative reception both at release and retrospectively.<ref name="FCM">{{cite news |title=5月10日号特別付録 ファミコンロムカセット オールカタログ |agency=Family Computer Magazine |issue=9 |publisher=[[Tokuma Shoten]] |date=May 10, 1991 |volume=7 |page=82 |language=ja}}</ref><ref name="Lambie">{{cite web |last1=Lambie |first1=Ryan |title=Transformers: Mystery of Convoy Might be the Most Cynical Licensed Video Game Ever Made |url=https://www.denofgeek.com/games/transformers-mystery-of-convoy-might-be-the-most-cynical-licensed-video-game-ever-made/ |website=[[Den of Geek]] |publisher=Den of Geek World |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200607202834/https://www.denofgeek.com/games/transformers-mystery-of-convoy-might-be-the-most-cynical-licensed-video-game-ever-made/ |archive-date=June 7, 2020 |date=February 13, 2018}}</ref><ref name="RGamer">{{cite web |author1=Retro Gamer Staff |title=Transformers: Convoy no Nazo (Transformers: Mystery of Convoy) |url=https://www.retrogamer.net/retro_games80/transformers-convoy-no-nazo-transformers-mystery-of-convoy/ |website=[[Retro Gamer]] |publisher=[[Imagine Publishing]] |access-date=October 26, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150913083230/https://www.retrogamer.net/retro_games80/transformers-convoy-no-nazo-transformers-mystery-of-convoy/ |archive-date=September 13, 2015 |date=February 11, 2010}}</ref> ''[[1UP.com]]'' called it the "perfect example of a shameless tie-in." They criticized the game for its high level of difficulty, the game's implementation of the transforming ability and how the ninth stage loops infinitely unless a specific pattern is followed.<ref name=1up/>

